<a name="2707"></a>



<div class="sponsorshipTitle">Day 27</div>
<br /><IMG height=200 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/Mango_Radio.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=5><STRONG>Mango Radio by Areaware&nbsp;- <EM>Wood</EM> you like to&nbsp;listen to this? We would!</STRONG><BR><A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5561461/Areaware/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Areaware</A> will exhibit its Mango wooden radio at the 2009 International CES. The Mango is hand-crafted from new growth wood in an Indonesian farming village, and for every tree that is used in production - a new one is planted. <BR><BR>This NYC-based company is known for its uniquely designed products that emphasize original expression, and this Mango wooden radio lives up to this reputation. <BR><BR>Singgih Kartono, the product's designer, chooses wood for his radios because of his appreciation of wood's organic vitality and simplicity, as well as its pleasing aesthetic look. The Magno combines the most current mp3 player compatible electronics with sustainably grown woods. Visit <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5561461/Areaware/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Areaware</A> in the LVCC, South Hall 1, Booth # 21725.
<br /><img width="1" height="4" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/><br /><a class="back_to_top" href="#">[back to top]</a>
