<div class="sponsorshipTitle">Day 28</div>
<br /><STRONG>Eye-Fi: Automatic, Wireless Picture Uploads</STRONG><BR><IMG height=59 hspace=8 src="/images/content/eye_fi_logo.gif" width=97 align=left><A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5769357/Eye-Fi/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Eye-Fi </A>is changing the way people take, save and share photos. All <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5769357/Eye-Fi/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Eye-Fi</A> digital camera memory cards come with everything needed to make it simple to set up and connect to a home Wi-Fi network. After that, consumers can simply pop the card into a digital camera and start capturing memories, knowing that they will automatically upload to their personal computer as soon as they return to the area of the wireless network. It's that easy. Visit <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5769357/Eye-Fi/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Eye-Fi</A> in the LVCC, South Hall, Booth #32024 at the 2009 International CES.
